I went there yesterday with 6 of my friends and had more people meeting me there to celebrate my birthday. Where should I begin... it wasn’t open at the time posted because the cook as well as bartenders weren’t there. People was standing outside in the rain. Finally we were allowed in around 6 and as we walked in we were cut off by the most obnoxious rude unprofessional bartender throwing metal reserve signs on the tables. We stopped to let her finish tossing the signs and went to 2 of the tables she left open I asked are the tables ok and she said yes. We sat down ordered food  and drinks and began enjoying my day. The place was empty there were only 2 other tables occupied and less than 5 people at the bar, the atmosphere was calm after 1 1/2 hours of enjoying ourselves 2 women arrive and the rude unprofessional bartender comes over and tells us to move our belongings from the table we were occupying because it’s reserved.. how can it be reserved after being occupied by me for 1 1/2 hours. Since I didn’t get her name I’ll describe her 5’7 170lbs black glasses hair up in ponytail hates her job. Andrew and Sonya were great but this woman belongs on the unemployment line. I couldn’t understand why we had to move when there were so many unoccupied empty tables. Then the bartender sent security over to explain the table was for regulars I didn’t want to hear it and the more he spoke I realized it was time to leave. There was no way I was gonna lower or degrade myself or my guests  by arguing or getting into it with fake security or anyone else but my dissatisfaction  was made clear my guests paid the tab and we left on the way out I saw my additional guests explained what happened and we went to another local bar and had drinks food and fun. After talking to other patrons I learned that happens a lot in 95 South. The owner of this bar needs to reevaluate the employees and it’s practices why make people move when there are more than 10 tables empty. My intentions were to leave by 9 but instead I was thrown out at 730.  I’ve been there before overlooked the creeps and hoodrats because the drinks and food are good but never again. It was obvious we weren’t the regular crowd we had teeth our clothes weren’t sagging and we were articulate. Avoid this place and spare yourself the frustration disrespect and inconvenience myself and my guests experienced. Try Sweet Brooklyn, 704 or Essence to name a few.
